To get the most out of FlawBOT's commands, modify the included config.json file with below API tokens.

Download the latest FlawBOT source code. Open FlawBOT\src\FlawBOT.sln in Visual Studio. Modify the included config.json file with your API tokens. Build the project. dotnet clean -c Release dotnet restore dotnet build -c Release -f net7.0 dotnet publish -c Release -f net7.0 Update your Raspberry Pi to the latest version. sudo apt-get update -y sudo apt-get upgrade -y Copy the compiled FlawBOT files to the Raspberry Pi. Install .NET Core 7.0 runtime. curl -sSL https://dot.net/v1/dotnet-install.sh | bash /dev/stdin --channel Current echo 'export DOTNET_ROOT=$HOME/.dotnet' >> ~/.bashrc echo 'export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/.dotnet' >> ~/.bashrc source ~/.bashrc Navigate to where you've copied your FlawBOT files and start the bot. dotnet FlawBOT.dll

Lavalink is a standalone audio sending node. It's required to use FlawBOT's music commands. The latest version of Lavalink is included with FlawBOT, however it still needs to be configured and enabled. Open application.yml and change address to the IP of a machine you'll be running Lavalink from. server: # REST and WS server port: 2333 address: 192.168.2.38 Open config.json and change Address to match the address set in Step 1. Set Enabled to true. "Lavalink": { "Enabled": true, "Address": "192.168.2.38", "Port": 2333, "Password": "youshallnotpass" } Open the command prompt and start Lavalink by entering: java -jar Lavalink.jar note In case of errors, install the latest Java Development Kit.
Commands for directly interacting with FlawBOT.
Returns basic information about FlawBOT. /bot info
Removes FlawBOT from the server. Requires administrative permissions on the server. /bot leave
Pings the active FlawBOT instance. /bot ping
Returns the uptime of the active FlawBOT instance. /bot uptime
Owner Only. Changes FlawBOT's activity. /bot activity Team Fortress 2
Owner Only. Changes FlawBOT's avatar. /bot avatar https://frinkiac.com/img/S03E20/301341.jpg
Owner Only. Changes FlawBOT's server nickname. /bot nickname FlowBOT
Owner Only. Changes FlawBOT's status to Online, Idle, DND or Offline. /bot status Idle
Commands for interacting with the Imgur API.
Returns a queried image from Imgur. /imgur cats
Removes messages from the current server channel. /channel clean 10
Returns information about a server channel. /channel info #text
Creates a new channel category. /channel new-category Welcome
Creates a new text channel. /channel text texts
Creates a new voice channel. /channel voice voices
Changes the server channel name. /channel rename #text newtext
Changes the server channel topic. /channel topic Watermelon picking
Commands for interacting with the Urban Dictionary API.
Returns a definition for a word of phrase from Urban Dictionary. /define computers
Commands for playing audio in voice channels using Lavalink.
Returns the current audio track information. /music info
Plays audio from a URL or search query. /music play https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4JkIs37a2JE
Stops audio playback and leave the voice channel. /music stop
Changes audio playback volume between 0% and 100%. /music volume 50
Commands for interacting with the NASA API.
Returns the Picture of the Day from NASA. /nasa
Commands for interacting with the News API.
Commands for interacting with Nintendo game APIs.
Returns information about an Amiibo figurine or card. /amiibo luigi
Asks the magic 8-ball a question. /ask Am I lucky?
Returns a random cat fact and image. /cat
Commands for interacting with the OMDB API.
Returns a movie or TV show from OMDB. /omdb mission impossible
Commands for interacting with the Reddit RSS Feed.
Returns hot-topics from Reddit for a given subreddit. /reddit hot tf2
Returns new-topics from Reddit for a given subreddit. /reddit new tf2
Returns top-topics from Reddit for a given subreddit. /reddit top tf2
Creates a new server role. /role create admin
Deletes a server role. /role delete admin
Returns server role information. /role info admin
Returns list of users in a given role. /role inrole admin
Toggles whether the role can be mentioned by others. /role mention admin
Commands for managing the Discord server.
Changes the name of the server. /server rename Cool Discord Server
Commands for interacting with Frinkiac and Morbotron.
Returns a random Simpsons episode GIF. /simpsons
Returns a random Futurama episode GIF. /futurama
Commands for interacting with the Speedrun.com API.
Returns game information from Speedrun.com /speedrun Donkey Kong 64
Commands for interacting with the Teamwork.TF API for Team Fortress 2.
Returns a community creator profile from teamwork.tf /tf2 creator criticalflaw
Returns an item from the latest TF2 item schema. /tf2 item natasha
Returns map information from teamwork.tf /tf2 map pl_upward
Returns the latest news article from teamwork.tf /tf2 news
Returns a game server with given ip address. /tf2 search 164.132.233.16
Returns a list of servers for a given game-mode. /tf2 server payload
Returns a curated list of servers. /tf2 server-list
Commands for interacting with the Steam API.
Formats a server connection string into a link. /steam connect 192.168.0.200
Returns information on a Steam game. /steam game Team Fortress 2
Returns information on a Steam user. /steam user criticalflaw
Commands for interacting with the Twitch API.
Returns Twitch stream information, if online. /twitch jerma985
Commands for interacting with the WeatherStack API.
Returns weather information for a given location. /weather toronto
Returns server user's profile picture. /user avatar @CriticalFlaw
Bans a server user for a given day duration and reason. /user ban @CriticalFlaw 7 Spammer
Unbans a user from the server. /user unban 1234567
Commands for interacting with the Wikipedia API.
Returns articles found on Wikipedia. /wikipedia discord
Commands for interacting with the YouTube API.
Returns a list of queried YouTube channels. /youtube channel Jerma2nd
Returns a list of queried YouTube playlists. /youtube playlist gmod
Returns the first YouTube search result. /youtube search tf2
Returns a list of queried YouTube videos. /youtube video tf2

Install .NET Core 7.0 Runtime for console apps. Download the latest version of flawbot.zip. Extract downloaded file contents into a separate folder. Modify the included config.json file with your API tokens. Open the command prompt and start the bot by entering: dotnet FlawBOT.dll

The following is a list of modules included with the latest version of FlawBOT. Bot - Basic commands for interacting directly with the bot. Channel - Commands for managing server channels. Dictionary - Commands for interacting with the Urban Dictionary API. Imgur - Commands for interacting with the Imgur API. Misc - Miscellenaous bot interaction commands. Music - Have the bot play music in a voice channel. NASA - Commands for interacting with the NASA API. News - Commands for interacting with the News API. Nintendo - Commands for interacting with the Nintendo game APIs. OMDB - Commands for interacting with the OMDB API. Reddit - Commands for interacting with the Reddit RSS feeds. Role - Commands for managing server roles. Server - Commands for managing the Discord server. Simpsons - Commands for interacting with Frinkiac and Morbotron. Speedrun - Commands for interacting with the Speedrun.com API. Steam - Commands for interacting with the Steam API. Team Fortress 2 - Commands for interacting with the Teamwork.TF API for TF2. User - Commands for managing server users. Weather - Commands for interacting with the WeatherStack API. Wikipedia - Commands for interacting with the Wikipedia API. YouTube - Commands for interacting with the YouTube API.
